   "source": [
    "\n",
    "# Tutorial: Traj Preprocessing\n",
    "\n",
    "**The following notebook illustrate the `TrajPreprocessing` class how to run the preprocessing steps.**\n",
    "- **Several preprocessing steps are available for the tail angle**:\n",
    "  - Interpolating missing values\n",
    "  - Apply 1â‚¬ filter\n",
    "\n",
    "- **The kinematic vigor is also computed from the speed and will also be useful for segmentation into bouts**:\n",
    "\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* Loading dependencies"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from IPython.display import SVG, display\n",
    "\n",
    "import os\n",
    "import numpy as np\n",
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "from megabouts.tracking_data.tracking_data import TrackingConfig\n",
    "from megabouts.tracking_data.load_example import load_example_data\n",
    "from megabouts.tracking_data.tracking_data import FullTrackingData\n",
    "\n",
    "from megabouts.preprocessing.traj_preprocessing import TrajPreprocessingConfig\n",
    "from megabouts.preprocessing.traj_preprocessing import TrajPreprocessingResult\n",
    "from megabouts.preprocessing.traj_preprocessing import TrajPreprocessing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Loading Data"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* TrackingConfig and TrackingData similar to [tutorial_Loading_Data](./tutorial_Loading_Data.ipynb)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_recording, fps, mm_per_unit = load_example_data('fulltracking_posture')\n",
    "\n",
    "tracking_cfg = TrackingConfig(fps=fps, tracking='full_tracking')\n",
    "\n",
    "head_x = df_recording['head_x'].values*mm_per_unit\n",
    "head_y = df_recording['head_y'].values*mm_per_unit\n",
    "head_yaw = df_recording['head_angle'].values\n",
    "tail_angle = df_recording.filter(like='tail_angle').values\n",
    "\n",
    "tracking_data = FullTrackingData.from_posture(head_x = head_x,\n",
    "                                              head_y = head_y,\n",
    "                                              head_yaw = head_yaw,\n",
    "                                              tail_angle = tail_angle)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "from megabouts.utils.utils_downsampling import create_downsampling_function\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df_recording, fps, mm_per_unit = load_example_data('fulltracking_posture')\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "head_x = df_recording['head_x'].values*mm_per_unit\n",
    "head_y = df_recording['head_y'].values*mm_per_unit\n",
    "head_yaw = df_recording['head_angle'].values\n",
    "tail_angle = df_recording.filter(like='tail_angle').values\n",
    "\n",
    "fps = 60\n",
    "downsampling_f, _, _, _ = create_downsampling_function(fps, 700, len(head_x) * 1000 / 700)\n",
    "head_x = downsampling_f(head_x, axis=0)\n",
    "head_y = downsampling_f(head_y, axis=0)\n",
    "head_yaw = downsampling_f(head_yaw, axis=0)\n",
    "tail_angle = downsampling_f(tail_angle, axis=0)\n",
    "\n",
    "tracking_cfg = TrackingConfig(fps=fps, tracking='full_tracking')\n",
    "\n",
    "tracking_data = FullTrackingData.from_posture(head_x = head_x,\n",
    "                                              head_y = head_y,\n",
    "                                              head_yaw = head_yaw,\n",
    "                                              tail_angle = tail_angle)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Run Preprocessing"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "* Define preprocessing config"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 17,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "traj_preprocessing_cfg = TrajPreprocessingConfig(fps=tracking_cfg.fps)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 18,
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "traj_df_input = tracking_data.traj_df\n",
    "\n",
    "traj = TrajPreprocessing(traj_preprocessing_cfg).preprocess_traj_df(traj_df_input)"
   ]
  },

   "source": [
    "t = np.arange(tracking_data.T)/tracking_cfg.fps\n",
    "IdSt = np.random.randint(tracking_data.T)\n",
    "Duration = 10*tracking_cfg.fps\n",
    "\n",
    "t_win = t[IdSt:IdSt+Duration]-t[IdSt]\n",
    "fig,ax = plt.subplots(2,1,figsize=(10,7),sharex=True)\n",
    "ax[0].plot(t_win,traj.x[IdSt:IdSt+Duration],label='raw position')\n",
    "ax[0].plot(t_win,traj.x_smooth[IdSt:IdSt+Duration],label='smooth position')\n",
    "ax[1].plot(t_win,traj.vigor[IdSt:IdSt+Duration],label='trajectory vigor')\n",
    "ax[0].set(ylabel='x position (mm)')\n",
    "ax[1].set(ylabel='vigor (A.U.)')\n",
    "ax[1].set(xlabel='frame number')\n",
    "\n",
    "for i in range(2):\n",
    "    ax[i].legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Tuning [1â‚¬ filter](https://gery.casiez.net/1euro/)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "> &#x1F4DD;\t\n",
    "> There are two configurable parameters in the filter, the minimum cutoff frequency `freq_cutoff_min` and the speed coefficient `beta`.\\\n",
    "> Decreasing the minimum cutoff frequency decreases slow speed jitter. Increasing the speed coefficient decreases speed lag.\\\n",
    "> The parameters are set using two-step procedure:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Step 1**\n",
    "\n",
    "**`beta` is set to 0 and `freq_cutoff_min` to 10Hz. Focus on a part of the recording where the fish is not swimming or swimming at low speed.\\\n",
    " `freq_cutoff_min` is adjusted to remove jitter and preserve an acceptable lag during these slow movements.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 21,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-input"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "IdSt = 100\n",
    "Duration = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "x = traj.x\n",
    "x_smooth = TrajPreprocessing.one_euro_filter(x,freq_cutoff_min=10000,beta = 0, rate = tracking_cfg.fps)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,1,figsize=(15,4),sharex=True)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Tuning '+ r'$\\text{freq_cutoff_min}$'+ ' during slow movement')\n",
    "ax.plot(x[IdSt:IdSt+Duration],label='raw position')\n",
    "ax.plot(x_smooth[IdSt:IdSt+Duration],label='smoothed position')\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel='frame number',ylabel='x position (mm)')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "&#x2705;\t Here a value close to 10Hz for `freq_cutoff_min` allows to smooth while keeping an acceptable lag*"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### **Step 2**\n",
    "\n",
    "**Focus on a part of the recording where the fish is moving fast. Adjust `beta` with a focus on minimizing lag.**"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 22,
   "metadata": {
    "tags": [
     "hide-input"
    ]
   },
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1500x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "IdSt = 2300\n",
    "Duration = 100\n",
    "\n",
    "x = traj.x\n",
    "x_smooth = TrajPreprocessing.one_euro_filter(x,freq_cutoff_min=8,beta=1.4,rate=tracking_cfg.fps)\n",
    "\n",
    "fig,ax = plt.subplots(1,1,figsize=(15,4),sharex=True)\n",
    "ax.set_title('Tuning '+ r'$\\text{beta}$'+ ' during fast movement')\n",
    "ax.plot(x[IdSt:IdSt+Duration],label='raw position')\n",
    "ax.plot(x_smooth[IdSt:IdSt+Duration],label='smoothed position')\n",
    "ax.set(xlabel='frame number',ylabel='x position (mm)')\n",
    "ax.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "&#x2705;\t*Here we selected `beta=1.4`*"
   ]
  }
